race.comment: Quite a few horses in this race return to SA after tackling harder races in Melbourne during the spring. The fresh horse on the scene is WIGGUM (5), who returned from a spell to win over 1050m. His second-up record doesn't read as well but he looks well-placed with a big weight drop and the extra 150m. He can go on with it here and looks a key winning chance. ZOUPURRING (7) has been flying this campaign with three wins from four starts. He is undefeated at this track and distance, has a low draw and no weight so he ticks plenty of boxes. KARAVAS (6) is an each-way chance in this - she can mix her form but her best is clearly good enough to win. MT NISEKO (9) must be given strong consideration, as does SIR NOW (4) who boasts a great winning strike rate but is yet to tick the 1200m box.
